  "text": "The TiO 2 nanofillers incorporated in the final post formulation distinctly contributed to off-setting the yellow coloration due to Kevlar fibers ( Fig. 1) and additionally enhanced the radiopacity, an important requirement for endodontic posts. The weight fraction of the filler was selected on the basis of optimal mechanical properties and radiographic appearance. The experimental K FRC exhibited excellent radiopacity (3.9 mm Al equivalent) to function as an endodontic post. Ideally, the radiodensity of a post material must be higher than that of dentine (1 mm Al) and similar to or slightly greater than that of enamel (2 mm Al) to facilitate their radiographic detection [CITATION_1] . In contrast, everStick ® POST failed to meet this requirement with significantly lower value at 0.9 mm Al, which was similar to that reported by Dündar et al. 32) . The titanium oxide also increased the flexural strength and modulus by about 14% (Table  1) due to the dispersion of these particles between fiber filaments, which increases the bending resistance.",
